Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing and specifically focuses on inducing hypernym relationships.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper introduces a novel neural network architecture designed to enforce certain properties as soft constraints.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper involves training a neural network to learn hypernymy relations.
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is relevant as the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed method on various benchmarks across different tasks.
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is less likely but still possible as the paper introduces a new type of network architecture.
